This paper is primarily concerned with security and privacy issues in Vehicular Communication (VC) systems, specifically the Vehicular Public-Key Infrastructure (VPKI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses issues related to network infrastructure and scalability, which suggests that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another likely sub-category. The paper also presents an implementation of the VPKI, which suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses user privacy protection, which suggests that cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
